place.name: TRENEGLOS
place.gazetteerText: TRENEGLOS, a parish in Launceston district, Cornwall; 8½ miles W by N of Launceston r. station. Post town, Launceston. Acres, 2,730. Real property, £1,188. Pop., 138. Houses, 31. The manor belongs to J. Braddon, Esq. The living is a vicarage, united with Warbstow, in the diocese of Exeter. Value, £187.* Patron, the Prince of Wales. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
